.3 g","calories":"2092 kJ \/ 500 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 round cake tins (Ø 20 cm), baking paper, skewer, wire rack, oven","hintsAndTricks":["One of the most traditional afternoon tea treats. The bitterness of the coffee flavour is perfectly offset by the sweetness of the buttercream icing, and the walnuts give it a lovely crunch. It’s a homely cake, yet a showstopper."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 10m","10 slices"]}